Key Match Events: Willey Adames hit a 3-run home run in the 3rd inning.
Noelvi Marte missed a home run opportunity in the 8th inning when Blake Perkins caught the ball on the warning track.
Jackson Chourio hit a solo home run in the 9th inning to give the Brewers the lead.
Post-Match Reflections: Ty France hit a hard grounder that was caught by Brewers' first baseman Jake Bauers to end the game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Brewers went 1-15 with runners in scoring position.
Cincinnati didn't do much better, going 1-10 with runners in scoring position.
The Reds still haven't had a hit against Devin Williams since Alejo Lopez had an infield single in 2022.
Others: Elly De La Cruz drew a 2-out walk in the 9th inning to represent the winning run at first base.
Blake Perkins made an incredible diving catch on a potential walk-off hit by Ty France in the 9th inning.
